{"name":"Business Models","id":239,"content":"<p>Revenue Streams</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 1 or more, streams (ways in which your money goes, and money comes)</p>\n\n<p>Revenue Model:&nbsp; A strategy of managing Revenue Streams.</p>\n\n<p>Business Model: Revenu Model + more</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>How do you get customers?</p>\n\n<div style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; padding-bottom:10px; border-bottom: 1px solid black; display: inline-block; font-size: larger;\">\n<p><strong>Acquisition Models</strong></p>\n</div>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Make people aware about your service/product. Analyse which channels are suitable, and good way to engage with those channels.</li>\n\t<li>Make them consider your product/service (help them compare, help them make decision, etc)</li>\n\t<li>Help them have an easy onboarding to your service/product platform. (Make things easily accessible for them)</li>\n\t<li>Retain customers that you have acquired. Generate leads from existing/prospective customers.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Marketing:</p>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li>Content Marketing (Blogging, Ebooks, Guides, Videos etc)</li>\n\t<li>Social Media Marketing</li>\n\t<li>Search Marketing</li>\n\t<li>Email Marketing</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><strong>Freemium Model:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Initially spend money to grab customers, provide <em>some</em>&nbsp;aspects of service for free.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Look-Alike Model:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Find customers similar (based on different factors) similar to your best customers. Target those.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Response Model:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Identify who is responding (by purachase, or by following your activities e.g. on social media, who opens and reads your email etc). Identify prospects (those who are not your customer but are likely to be).</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Sources: <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/service/customer-acquisition\">[1]</a>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>How do you generate revenue?</p>\n\n<h2>Types of Revenue Models:</h2>\n\n<p><strong>Subscription-Based:</strong></p>\n\n<p>You provide some Service, and charge an amount per month/year/whatever.</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Increase customer satisfaction,</li>\n\t<li>hold customers to the service,</li>\n\t<li>make people aware about their need for the service, or manufacture the need for service,</li>\n\t<li>hunt people who need your service,</li>\n\t<li>make people transition from other&#39;s service by giving competitive price/quality/whatever.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Ad-Based:&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Revenue Streams of Paytm:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Commissions (%age on transactions made to seller, Commission on <em>recharges</em>)</li>\n\t<li>Escrow Accounts (From Paytm Wallet: You store money, paytm uses that money in other investments (safest way in banks where it will earn interest)</li>\n\t<li>Digital Golds</li>\n\t<li>Ecommerce (Onboard sellers on the platform and earn commission from them.)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Sources: <a href=\"https://bstrategyhub.com/paytm-business-model-how-does-paytm-make-money/\">[1]</a>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<h2>Types of Business Models</h2>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n","authorId":null,"subject":"finance","tags":null,"img":null,"summary":"string","lastUpdated":"2020-07-29T10:25:09.945+0000"}